    ref:'Psalm 46:10',
    imgQuery:'Siargao coconut trees island nature Philippines',
    reflection:'The pace of earlier years does not allow for stillness. Everything demands urgency. But as life slows, God extends an invitation that was always open but rarely received: be still. Not passive. Not resigned. But fully present — to God, to the people who love you, to the moment you are actually in. The gift of slowing down is one of the most underrated gifts of the second half.',
